					  Schuler Wins Second Consecutive OPGA Mid-Am  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  June 22, 2010    No Comments  

					 

 Dan Schuler of Springfield, Ohio won the 2010 Ohio Public Golf Association’s Mid-Amateur Championship today at the Chapel Hill Golf Course in Mt. Vernon. His 36-hole total of 147 was good for a 1-shot victory over Ryan Zahn of Lexington.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Haley Wins Ohio Publinx  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  August 7, 2009    No Comments  

					 

 Final results from the 2009 Ohio Public Links Championship, the 81st playing of this statewide amateur event. This year, the tournament was played at Cook’s Creek Golf Club in Ashville, Ohio with a starting entry of 137 players. David Haley’s 7-under par total was good for a one-shot victory. Results of the 59 players who made the cut: 
 281    HALEY, JR.    DAVID    Hilliard 
282    BALLINGER    TOM    Mansfield 
283    LEEDS    JASON    Westerville 
283    LOWER    JUSTIN    Canal Fulton 
283    STOCKE    RYAN    Boardman     [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

