					  Savage Wins 2009 Ohio Publinx Mid-Am  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  June 23, 2009    No Comments  

					 

 After running out with a strong 67 in round one, Scott Savage of Mt. Vernon held on to a one-shot victory over a hard-charging Dan Schuler of Springfield in this year’s OPGA Mid-Am Championship. 
 Complete final results from the 2009 Ohio Public Golf Association’s Mid-Amateur Tournament, held at  Chapel Hill Golf Course in Mt. Vernon, June 22-23, 2009:   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  2008 Ohio Public Links Championship  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  August 8, 2008    No Comments  

					 

 Brad Wright of Cambridge won the 2008 Ohio Publinx at Cooks Creek GC in Ashville, Ohio, August 5th – 8th, with a 72-hole total of 278. Complete scores are posted  here on the OPGA website . 
 – Allen Freeman  
    

					 

					   

			

					
			

