					  2008 Ohio Public Links Championships  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  March 20, 2008    No Comments  

					 

 Play in the Ohio Publinx! The Ohio Public Golf Association announces their 2008 tournament schedule, the association’s 80th anniversary. These events are open to all male Ohio resident golfers, public or private: 
 OPGA MID-AMATEUR STATE CHAMPIONSHIP 
June 23 – 24, 2008 
CHAPEL HILL GOLF COURSE, MT. VERNON, OHIO 
36 Hole Scratch Stroke Play Event – Ages 25 & Up 
$75 entry fee due June 7 
 DOWNLOAD ENTRY FORM  (Word document) 
 OPGA STATE AMATEUR CHAMPIONSHIP 
August 5 – 8, 2008 
COOKS CREEK GOLF COURSE, ASHVILLE, OHIO 
72 Holes Scratch Stroke Play Event 
Practice Round Monday, August 4, 2008 
$125 entry fee due July 15 
 DOWNLOAD ENTRY FORM  (Word document) 
 OHIO MEMORIAL SENIORS CHAMPIONSHIP 
September 13 -14, 2008 
HIAWATHA GOLF COURSE,  MT. VERNON, OHIO 
Practice Round on September 12, 2008 
36 Holes – Ages 50 & Up – 6 Age Flights 
$75 entry fee due September 1 
 DOWNLOAD ENTRY FORM  (Word document) 
 Additional information and entries may be obtained from any OPGA director, OPGA Secretary Bob Martin at 440-239-9747, or OPGA President Ken Hyland at 330-875-4196. Or visit the OPGA website at  http://www.opga.us/  
 –Allen Freeman 
    

					 

					   

			

					
			

				 

			

				
 
	  
 


			

			
			

			 



			 

	 

 

